2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents lower bounds on the size of uniform non-constant depth threshold circuits for the permanent, which involves the study of algorithms and data structures. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper involves the study of discrete mathematical objects such as circuits and their properties. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper may involve the study of information theory concepts such as entropy and information content. 
5. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper may involve the study of logical circuits and their properties.
